                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/1335: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-18T16:00:00-06:00"
                            >February 18, 1932—4 p.m.</date>]<lb/>[Received 6 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conference between Government and Castristas now under way at Legation, firing
                    stopped at 1 p.m., and many Castrista troops have handed in arms. Insurrection
                    believed over. Further details later.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
